    - target: {fileID: 1497534752906518004, guid: b3ad3ffe5d9ec684084b142d99857b31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: GameText
      value: "<b>Computer Bismarck (Strategic Simulations, 1980)</b>\n\n2d Turn-based
        strategy game by Strategic Simulations (SSI) in 1980. \n\nBased on the last
        battle of the German battleship Bismarck in the Atlantic. \n\n-Takes place
        on a 2d Atlantic Ocean\n-Player controls British forces against the German
        units\n-can be controlled by the computer or another player. -6 different
        game modes. \n-The game ends when the player sinks the Bismarck, or when
        the number of rounds runs out. (Baker, 2023)\n\n-The reasons that war games
        and computer games became so popular on pc. (Bob Proctor, 1988). \n"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1497534752906518004, guid: b3ad3ffe5d9ec684084b142d99857b31, type: 3}
