    - target: {fileID: 1497534752906518004, guid: b3ad3ffe5d9ec684084b142d99857b31, type: 3}
      propertyPath: GameText
      value: "<b>1996 - Pok\xE9mon Red and Pok\xE9mon Blue.</b> (Game Freak, 1996).\n\n-Navigate
        the world of Kanto to master Pok\xE9mon Battling. \n-Defeat 8 Gym Leaders
        and the 4 best Leaders using creatures called Pok\xE9mon \n-Capture and collect
        all 151 Pok\xE9mon in the game and complete the Pokedex. \n\n-Battles are
        turn-based, and different Pok\xE9mon have different abilities (Pokemon Red
        - Game Boy Review at IGN, n.d.)\n\n-To collect all the Pok\xE9mon, players
        need to connect to other <b>Game Boys</b> using the <b>Game Link Cable</b>
        and use game\u2019s multiplayer trading between the two games. \n\n-Popularised
        turn-based genre by introducing younger audiences\n-And for their creature
        collecting and trading"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 1497534752906518004, guid: b3ad3ffe5d9ec684084b142d99857b31, type: 3}
